rivation, including getting the default timeline duration and calculating playhead percentage from tick values.\n\n2. A core hook will sync the playhead from the session using li_rt to set the playhead percentage, though an alternative approach involves having compose read directly from the session instead of li_rt_studio_timeline_playhead_pct().\n\n3. The C runtime needs to be updated with a new function li_rt_studio_timeline_set_playhead_pct() to support setting the playhead percentage.\n\nThe implementation will change `li_rt_studio_timeline_tick_frame` to use stored simulation tick or replace the flow in Li. The C runtime will be updated with new functions: `li_rt_studio_timeline_set_playhead_pct()` and `li_rt_studio_timeline_set_sim_tick()`. The mock increment in tick_frame will be deprecated, making tick_frame return 0 when not playing. Li functions will include `studio_timeline_duration_ticks_default()` returning 100 and `studio_timeline_playhead_pct_from_tick()` computing percentage from tick and duration.\n\n# clamp tick to [0, duration], return tick/duration as float\n\ndef studio_timeline_sync_playhead_from_tick(tick: int, duration: int) raises IO -> unit\n  # calls li_rt_studio_timeline_set_playhead_pct(studio_timeline_playhead_pct_from_tick(...))\n\ndef studio_timeline_reset_for_sim(sim_out: var SimSessionStub) raises IO -> int\n  # sim_reset, sync playhead to 0, stop playing\n  sim_reset(sim_out)\n  studio_timeline_sync_playhead_from_tick(0, duration)\n  li_rt stop playing - need reset that doesn't use mock 0.35\n\ndef studio_timeline_tick_sim_step(config, sim_out, dt) raises IO -> intI'll implement the timeline-sim sync entirely in Li lib.li with minimal C runtime changes.\n\n1. Pure Li functions will handle playhead derivation, including getting the default timeline duration and calculating playhead percentage from tick values.\n\n2. A core hook will sync the playhead from the session using li_rt to set the playhead percentage, though an alternative 